{"poster":"[NEM SIKERÜLT KIOLVASNI]","date":"2017-05-16T05:26:21.283+0000","title":"Ping muting and more on the way","subforum":"The News Hour","up_votes":1,"down_votes":0,"body":"[ÜRES]","replies":[{"poster":"PuncakesssR","date":"2017-05-18T03:34:33.421+0000","up_votes":8,"down_votes":0,"body":"Hey guys, come and join the largest discord server in the OCE region with over 1.4k members! https://discord.gg/2PdgYXA","replies":[{"poster":"Aurophilic Aura","date":"2017-05-18T09:25:17.682+0000","up_votes":1,"down_votes":3,"body":"Yea can you stop randomly banning people dat would be nice.","replies":[{"poster":"Trin","date":"2017-05-18T10:22:32.506+0000","up_votes":1,"down_votes":0,"body":"No one gets randomly banned. People who have been banned have been banned for a reason.","replies":[{"poster":"Aurophilic Aura","date":"2017-05-25T06:14:00.603+0000","up_votes":1,"down_votes":1,"body":"if someone is talking and someone else talks and well and they talk to fast you ban them. Not even spam, just someone talking with someone. Weko","replies":[]}]}]}]},{"poster":"Verigey","date":"2017-05-17T11:39:07.461+0000","up_votes":8,"down_votes":0,"body":"Riot please. For ages. I have wanted one simple feature. A ping that shows the enemy has returned to their lane. We have MIA, but nothing for when they return... I have to quickly write \"re\" (not sure if anyone even still understands that). While typing, although it takes about 1-2 seconds, it leaves you vulnerable and although it may not seem like an issue, it can cause you to miss cs just to notify your team. Why isn't this \"Re-Entered Ping\" around?","replies":[]},{"poster":"Tameru","date":"2017-05-17T10:14:10.712+0000","up_votes":3,"down_votes":0,"body":"Maybe there should be a midway point for ping muting. Instead of entirely muting pings from that person, there could be a ping limit (like if they spam ? at you it only does 1 ping unless there's at least X seconds between pings)\r\n\r\nOr, have the X seconds between pings, unless they're different ping types or far away on map (Example, mid spams mia ping, then does an alert to top and bot. The end result would be the one mia ping and the two alert pings)","replies":[{"poster":"jadelink","date":"2017-05-17T11:40:22.090+0000","up_votes":1,"down_votes":0,"body":"The problem wiht trying to stop it is some of us (like me) often use a trail of 3 pings to indicate a direction and approximate location of incoming enemies.  When people are being pincered, that's 6 pings.","replies":[]}]},{"poster":"OutMagic","date":"2017-05-16T21:08:18.145+0000","up_votes":4,"down_votes":1,"body":"Finally can ping mute, that'll be nice C: and the new melody ping is cool, enough change to get your attention more that the team wants to do a certain objective, I like it :D","replies":[]},{"poster":"KT2792","date":"2017-05-16T22:56:54.944+0000","up_votes":5,"down_votes":2,"body":"'gg mid no ping mia'\r\nhe pinged it 3 times, he also warning pinged you twice\r\n'RITO FIX NOW'\r\n\r\ncalling it this will happen.","replies":[{"poster":"The Void Beast","date":"2017-05-17T05:48:30.537+0000","up_votes":2,"down_votes":1,"body":"I think there should be a ping thresh hold option, like only able to receive 2 pings within 10 seconds from each player. I feel that would be a lot better than ping muting.","replies":[{"poster":"MoNkEyFiReS","date":"2017-05-18T11:58:58.656+0000","up_votes":1,"down_votes":0,"body":"I agree, but It should only be with in the same area, like the mechanic they've just implemented now where on my way pings in the same area go up in pitch, you should only be able to ping an area twice. The reason being, plans and things can change on the fly. If you're pinging to attack the enemy tower twice and then suddenly realise they are back dooring, you wouldn't be able to ping that. Two is a good number though, don't need more than that.","replies":[{"poster":"The Void Beast","date":"2017-06-02T04:41:26.876+0000","up_votes":1,"down_votes":0,"body":"I really like this idea, have a ping thresh hold set, but that is for the individual ping types, so you could receive 2 mia pings, then 2 omw pings or danger pings from the same person. I think that's a much more effective way of dealing with ping spammers than just muting them.","replies":[]}]}]},{"poster":"Exarch Leona","date":"2017-05-18T06:28:15.764+0000","up_votes":1,"down_votes":0,"body":"Happened already in the games i've played today. Ya called it man.","replies":[]},{"poster":"Nikkip","date":"2017-05-17T09:49:20.259+0000","up_votes":1,"down_votes":0,"body":"I was just in game trying this out with my team, and I can confirm that ping muting is only one way. Unlike chat muting where muting someone means no messages will be seen by both sides, muting pings only affects the player that consciously hits the ping mute button.  ","replies":[]}]},{"poster":"TheDamsel","date":"2017-05-17T05:01:30.375+0000","up_votes":2,"down_votes":0,"body":"the 'on my way' ping escalation sounds awesome, great potential for greater team cohesion there 10/10","replies":[{"poster":"BobbyShmurdaVEVO","date":"2017-05-17T06:21:30.078+0000","up_votes":1,"down_votes":0,"body":"definitely ","replies":[]}]},{"poster":"agent2","date":"2017-05-17T10:18:17.097+0000","up_votes":1,"down_votes":1,"body":"hi...........................................................................................................................................................................................................................................................................................................................................................................................................................................................................................................................................................................................................................................................................................................................................